- the OSI model is refer to the standard of classification in the interconnection process
that describe how the data transfer in the netowrk starting from prepering the data in the sender
antil ogy to receiving and processing it on the receiver side.
and it classifed into 7 layer to show how devices communications work it isn't real leyers it just virtual
to have clean understanding.

"2- The OSI model is a conceptual model that characterizes the communication functions of a
telecommunication system without regard to their underlying internal structure and technology"

- OSI orgnaized:

From the lowest to the highest level
1. Physical Layer
2. Data link Layer (or Media Access Control)
3. Network Layer (also called Internet Layer)
4. Transport Layer
5. Session Layer
6.  Presentation Layer
7. Application Layer
